    h3 Spherical linear interpolation

    p Spherical linear interpolation (slerp) is an operation that, given two unit quaternions, q and r, and a parameter t in the range[0, 1], computes an interpolated quaternion. Unlike conventional linear interpolation, it produces evenly distributed samples along the arc, which is rather important for animations.
    
